2. Cut the sides of the apples away from the core and grate the apple leaving the skins on. (I used my food processor) Place in pot with the strawberries.
3. Juice a lemon until you get 1 1/2 tablespoons of juice and poor into the stock pot.
4. Pour the honey into the pot and stir.
5. Heat mixture on high until boiling stirring occasionally. As soon as the mixture begins to boil, reduce heat to medium low to simmer.

6. Simmer for approximately 15 minutes until the strawberries become soft. Using a potato masher, mash the strawberries so there are no recognizable sections. If you have an immersion blender, you can use this instead.

7. Simmer for another 15-45 minutes, stirring occasionally. The longer the mixture simmers, the thicker the consistency. (Remember, this will not be as thick as the consistency made with sugar and/or pectin).
8. Strawberry Honey Jam can either be placed in freezer safe jars, or canned using a water bath for 10 minutes.
9. Enjoy!

title: whiskey orange cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan. Preheat oven to 350*F.
Cream butter or margarine until light and fluffy; gradually beat in sugar. Blend well. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add sifted flour mixture to creamed butter/sugar alternately with OJ. Blend well. Add rind.
Pour into prepared pan and bake approximately 1 hour.
Meanwhile, combine whiskey mixture ingredients in small pan. Cook over medium heat until sugar is thoroughly blended.
Remove cake from oven and immediately punch holes in top of cake. Pour hot whiskey mixture over hot cake. Cool in pan.

title: chocolate coconut rainforest confections/ candies
directions: peel and chop 1 yucca root into chunks drop in boiling water. boil until yucca is tender easily stabbed with a fork. drain in a strainer tranfer yucca to a bowl mash till smooth. then make coconut confectioners sugar by :Place the coconut sugar and arrowroot into the dry container of your Vita-Mix or coffee grinder. Place the lid on tightly. Start on low speed and gradually work your way up to the highest speed. It will take a few minutes to powder the sugar. You can start and stop the machine if you need to. Just don't open the lid or you will have powdered sugar floating everywhere in the air! The dry container of the Vita-Mix is designed to keep dry ingredients moving and not get hot and cake to the bottom of the container.

Keep blending the sugar until it is all powdered and light brown in color. Keep the lid on for a few minutes to let it settle to the bottom. combine coconut confectioners sugar with yucca, coconut flakes and vanilla. drop heaping spoonfuls on wax paper. roll into balls and refigerate for 30 minutes to a hour. If mixture is too soft to refidgerate before shaping. dip in chocolate shell mix once coated lift out with tongs or fork onto wax paper or cake rack place candies in refidgerator to harden.

title: the ultimate chocolate layered reeses peanut butter cup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a stand or electric mixer add the cake mix, eggs, oil, water, sour cream, pudding mix, and chocolate chips. Beat until well combined, about 1 1/2 minutes. It will be thick. Pour evenly into 2 well greased 9 inch cake pans. Bake for 30-35 minutes until toothpick comes out cleanly. Let cool completely.

To prepare cream cheese frosting place softened cream cheese and butter in mixing bowl, beat on med-high speed until creamy smooth. Slowly beat in powdered sugar until a good spreading consistency forms. I used almost the entire bag of powdered sugar. Refrigerate for a good hour before frosting.

Turn cake onto wax paper with a large serrated knife cut each cake in half width wise to form four layers. Place one layer onto a cake stand and drizzle melted peanut butter over the top. Next spread a generous amount of cream cheese frosting over that. Place another cake layer on top and repeat peanut butter and frosting until top layer is placed. Spread remaining frosting over entire cake then top with halved peanut butter cups. Freeze the cake until serving.

title: oven apple oatmeal
directions: Preheat oven to 375.

In a saucepan, heat the milk on medium heat until very hot but not quite boiling; stir occasionally to prevent scorching. Stir in the oats, maple syrup, nutmeg, and apples and continue to cook for several minutes, just until the mixture returns to a boil. Remove from the heat.

Coat a casserole with cooking spray, and throw in the raisins and salt. Pour (carefully!) the milk mixture over and stir well. Bake for 30 minutes, until all of the liquid is absorbed and the oatmeal is creamy. It will puff up slightly when finished.
Stir well before serving.
Reheats leftovers in the microwave for a couple of minutes and stir in some milk to loosen it up.

title: aunt sue's stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees

Halve zucchinis lengthwise so that each half resembles a canoe. Hollow and remove seeds from zucchini canoes. Place canoes on a cookie sheet, hollow side facing up, and set aside. Chop zucchini pulp and set aside.
Cook meat in olive oil in a large sautee pan over medium to medium high heat until brown.
Add garlic and onion, green pepper, and reserved zucchini pulp. Sautee until vegetables are softened.
Add parsley, oregano, 8 ounces of tomato sauce, and bread crumbs. Remove from heat. Blend into a stuffing and fill each canoe with stuffing.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and top with remaining sauce. Top with slices of mozzarella.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350 degrees, and serve.

title: portuguese pasta fazool
directions: 1. Cook pasta al dente according to box directions then drain well & set aside
2. Fry bacon until crisp remove to paper towel to dry
3. In the bacon fat saute onions for 4-5 minutes or until onions are clear.
3. Add the sauce plus 1 can of water and bring to a boil.
4. Add the chorizo, salt, pepper and oregano then lower heat to a simmer and cook
50 minutes.
5. Drain and rinse chickpeas add to sauce and cook 10 more minutes.
6. Add pasta and bacon.
7. Cook 2 minutes, remove from heat and the gourmet meal is finished.

title: soy ginger dressing
directions: Add parsley, garlic, ginger to food processor and pulse. Turn on and slowly add 1/2 of oil. Blend until smooth. Transfer to mixing bowl and add honey, dijon and vinegar to bowl. Whip mixture. Slowly add remaining 1/2 oil. After mixed, add soy sauce and sesame oil. continue to whisk until blended. May use immersion blender

title: hawaiian meatball
directions: puree ingredients, simmer on low heat to thicken. serve over heated meatballs

title: infamous white chicken chilli
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 inch cubes.
In large saucepan or dutch oven, saute chicken, onion & garlic powder in oil until chicken is no longer pink.
Add beans, chicken base, chillies and seasoning. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat - simmer uncovered for 30 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in sour cream & whipping cream.
Serve with warm flour tortillas.

title: cheese rich bean dip
directions: Cream cream cheese and sour cream in a mixer.
Add tabasco sauce and taco sauce.
Stir in the beans and the cheese by hand. It will get very thick. Add as much cheese as you like (up to 2 cups each), but reserve enough to sprinkle a nice layer on top.
Put in serving casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour.
Serve immediately with sturdy tortilla chips for dipping (or assorted crudites if preferred).
Or, transfer baked contents to a crock pot to keep heated for a longer time.
If desired, provide small plates on the side so that each person can scoop a portion onto the plate.

title: smashed cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower until soft. While that's steaming, cut the garlic into thin slices and sautee until transparent. Transfer into a bowl when done. Add finished cauliflower into bowl with salt and pepper. Smash altogether until in starts to look like lumpy mashed potatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: combine chicken ses oil, chili sauce, garlic, ginger and lime juice in bowl. cover and ref rig 2 hours. Cook chicken on grill. cool slightly then cut into thin strips. Place in a large bowl, add the cabbage, snow peas, scallions , bell pepper and cilantro. Reserve.
Proapre dressing by placing all ingredients in blender and process till smooth. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use.
Toss the salad with 1/3 c of dressing, or as desired. Transfer to decorative bowl and serve immediately.

title: tilapia with lime herb butter
directions: lightly salt tilapia on both sides. sprinkle top side of fish evenly with old bay, set aside. In sm. bowl mix butter, salt, herbs the lime juice and pulp. using a rubber spatula works well for this. when thourly mixed take about 1 tsp of butter mixture and place on each filet. there will be about 1/2 of butter mixture left, you can save for a later use. spread butter out evenly on each filet. bake in a 400 degree oven for about 10 min. or until fish is opaque in the thickest part. Just before serving sprinkle each filet with lime zest if desired.

title: macaroni cheese ham and corn casserole
directions: Boil 8 ounces of macaroni in water to which you have added 1 teaspoon salt. When the mac is al dente add 1 cup (box) of frozen corn. Let it sit.

Fry 1/2 chopped onion in the oil and butter and when the onions are cooked add salt and pepper to taste and 1 rounded tablespoon flour and stir a couple of minutes then slowly stir in 1 1/2 cups warm milk and cook over low heat until it is saucey. Then add 4 ounces diced ham, and 6 ounces shredded cheddar cheese (any cheese works). (fyi-You can buy the ham and cheese already diced and already shredded)

Drain the mac and corn and put it into a 2 quart heavy duty throw away aluminum baking pan. Pour the cheese mixture over the macaroni and corn mixture and stir in thoroughly. If you like sprinkle the top with red pepper. Bake for 15 minutes in a 350 degree oven. Then just warm up again at the tailgate.

title: annas colossal ginger cookies
directions: In a large bowl, microwave-safe bowl, melt shortening for about 1 minute on high. Beat in sugar, egg and molasses.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour, salt, baking soda, cocoa, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, pepper and crystallized ginger.
With a wooden spoon, stir flour mixture into sugar mixture until thoroughly combined.

Using a 1/3 cup measure, scoop dough onto a dish. Place dish with dough scoops in refrigerator and chill thoroughly for at least 3 hours. To hasten the process, you may chill dough in freezer for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a cookie sheet with parchment.

Dip dough balls in crystal sugar (if using) and place sugar side up on parchment. Bake for 12 minutes. Lay a sheet of foil over cookies and continue baking for another 6-8 minutes for a total cook-time of 18-20 minutes.

title: maple old-fashioned
directions: Mix whiskey, maple syrup, bitters, and 1 tsp. water in an old-fashioned glass until syrup is dissolved. Add a single large ice cube, then garnish with orange peel.

title: carrots and brussels sprouts
directions: Cook shallot in 2 tablespoons butter in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, 1 to 2 minutes. Add carrots, Brussels sprouts, 3/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables begin to brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add water and cover skillet, then cook over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender, 5 to 8 minutes. Stir in vinegar, remaining tablespoon butter, and salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple cider vinaigrette
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small owl, stirring with the whisk. Gradually add oil, stirring constantly, stir in Shallots.
Candied pecans
feta cheese
granny smith apple

title: speakeasy sparkler
directions: In a pitcher, stir together calvados, ginger brandy and juice. Divide among 8 chilled glasses filled halfway with ice. Top each with sparkling cider, and garnish with ginger.

title: fried cardoons
directions: Discard any discolored outer stalks and small leaves from cardoons. Trim base, tips, and outermost stalks, removing strings from stalks with a vegetable peeler (as for celery), then cut cardoons crosswise into 2-inch pieces.
Soak cardoons in 2 quarts water with 1 tablespoon salt in a large bowl, chilled, at least 8 hours.

Drain cardoons. Transfer to a 6-quart pot, then generously cover with cold water and add 2 tablespoons salt. Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, until tender when pierced with a sharp knife, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain on several layers of paper towels and cool 5 minutes.
Heat about 1 1/2 inches oil to 360°F in a 4- to 5-quart heavy pot over medium heat.
Whisk together flour and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a shallow bowl. Whisk together eggs, water, and cheese in another shallow bowl.

Toss one fifth of cardoons (all at once) with flour, shaking off excess, then transfer to egg mixture and turn with a fork to coat. Lift out coated cardoons 2 at a time, letting excess drip off, then carefully drop into hot oil. When all of batch has been added, fry, turning occasionally, until golden, 2 to 4 minutes. Transfer with a slotted spoon to fresh paper towels to drain.
Coat and fry remaining cardoons in 4 batches. (Return oil to 360°F between batches.) Season with salt.

title: rosa's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt in a large bowl. Add chilled butter and toss to coat. Work butter into flour mixture with your fingers until mixture resembles coarse meal with several pea-size pieces of butter remaining.
Using a fork, gently mix in buttermilk, then gently knead just until dough comes together (do not overmix).

Pinch off pieces of dough and gently roll into 1" balls; place on 2 parchment-lined baking sheets, spacing 2" apart (you should have about 24). If butter softens too much while you are working, chill dough until firm before baking, 15-20 minutes.
Bake biscuits until golden brown, 25-30 minutes. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with more salt. Serve warm.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes about one inch cubes - peeled or not
As much onion as you want to use, chopped
Boil potatoes and onions in a sauce pan until potatoes are just done
Pour off water - no need to strain
Turn down heat add salt, pepper, baking soda and butter.
Once butter is mostly melted, add milk to about 1/3 to 1/2 the depth of the potatoes in the sauce pan and cook until it starts to thicken.
Add corn starch to thicken to a medium thick sauce.
You may want to add more salt and pepper now and a little garlic if desired.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook minute rice according to instructions. Cool to room temperature.
Add frozen peas and celery. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Combine all dressing ingredients in a coverable container and shake to mix well. Add to rice and combine well.

title: ham, pear, leek & sourdough stuffing
directions: Bake cubed sourdough on a cookie sheet til dried out in a 200 oven. Let cool.
Melt 1 stick butter in a saute pan and add leeks and saute til limp add ham and cook 5 min til heated through. Add thyme salt & pepper and let cool.

When ready to bake combine bread cubes to wet mixture adding pears and chicken broth to moisten. Toss with parsley and put into a buttered casserole. Bake at 350 for 40 minutes covered with foil then 10 more min uncovered

title: spicy crockpot thai chicken
directions: Place chicken (trimmed of visible fat) into slow cooker.
Mix together peanut butter, lime juice, soy sauce, ginger, sweet chili sauce and sambal oelek. Our over chicken.
Cook on Low 8 hours or on High 4 hours.
Serve 1 piece of chicken and sauce with chopped peanuts and cilantro as garnish.
Weight Watchers = 6 points per serving
Wonderful with a 1/2 cup of rice on the side.
Remember that you won't be using all the sauce, so the calories and fat that are listed are higher than what you will actually be eating!

title: bbc couscous salad w/mint, raisins, almonds
directions: Combine dressing ingreds in blender and reserve
Prepare couscous according to directions on box.
Soak raisins in warm water for 10 minutes, then drain.
Combine salad ingreds with dressing to taste and toss. Reserve remaining dressing,

title: coconut custard pie
directions: In a saucepan, cobine milk, cream and butter. bring to simmer. Meanwhle, lightly beat eggs, and gradually beat in sugar, beating until thick.slowly pour milk mixture into egg mixture, stirring constantly. stir in vanilla. sprinkle coconut on bottom of crust. pour in enough filling mixture to cover coconut, sprinkle on optional nutmeg. bake 10 minutes at 450 degrees, then lower temp to 350. continue baking 20 minutes or until custard is set. cook to room temp befoe serving.
